title: Watch live: SpaceX preps for Falcon 9 test-firing in Florida
summary: SpaceX is preparing for a test-firing of a Falcon 9 rocket at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center at 9 a.m. EDT (1300 GMT) Saturday in preparation for liftoff Sunday with the company’s next batch of Starlink internet satellites. The rocket’s nine Merlin engines will fire for about seven seconds while hold-down clamps keep the Falcon 9 firmly on the ground at pad 39A. The Falcon 9 is set to lift off Sunday at 9:38 a.m. EDT (1338 GMT) with 53 Starlink internet satellites, marking SpcaeX’s 33rd launch of the year, and the 53rd dedicated launch for the Starlink network. title: SpaceX test-fires Falcon 9 rocket for Sunday launch from Florida
summary: SpaceX test-fired a Falcon 9 rocket at NASA’s Kennedy Space Center at 9 a.m. EDT (1300 GMT) Saturday in preparation for liftoff Sunday with the company’s next batch of Starlink internet satellites.

title: SpaceX to continue Starlink deployment with Starlink 4-25 mission
summary: SpaceX is set to launch the Starlink 4-25 mission Sunday, with liftoff scheduled for 9:38 AM EDT (13:38 UTC). A Falcon 9 rocket will carry another 53 satellites for the Starlink internet constellation, each with a mass of approximately 300 kilograms. The satellites will be deployed into an initial orbit of about 230 by 340 kilometers in altitude at an inclination of 53.2 degrees, separating from the second stage of the launch vehicle slightly more than 15 minutes after liftoff.
